        "desc": "The sounds of the city recede slightly when one enters the great library of\nCaras Galadhon. Much of the great tree is used to create the walls and the\nceiling of this house of knowledge. Great boughs arch high above, forming a vast\ndome of whispering green or golden leaves. The grey bole of the mallorn,\ntogether with screens and curtains hanging from the lower branches, helps shield\nthe large chamber from the activities on the talan outside. Bookshelves and\ntables stand in ranks, filled with knowledge, both ancient and newly gained.\n",
